articles.author: Nadeem Badshah
articles.title: Woman wins UK cheese rolling race despite being knocked unconscious - The Guardian
articles.description: ‘It feels great,’ said Canadian Delaney Irving, victor of the women’s race at Coopers Hill, near Gloucester
articles.content:
A woman was knocked unconscious while running down a hill to chase a 3kg (7lb) cheese wheel, but still managed to win her race at the bank holiday event.
